{
  "texts": [
    "This everyday notion was analysed and introduced into the philosophical lexicon by Harry Frankfurt.",
    "2 Frankfurt understands bullshit to be characterized not by an intent to deceive but instead by a reckless disregard for the truth.",
    "A student trying to sound knowledgeable without Bullshit (general) Any utterance produced where a speaker has indifference towards the truth of the utterance.",
    "Hard bullshit Bullshit produced with the intention to mislead the audience about the utterer's agenda.",
    "Soft bullshit Bullshit produced without the intention to mislead the hearer regarding the utterer's agenda."
  ]
}